duplicate the `ObjectImporter` class. But using dynamic loading with Native Image could cause issues, so I'll handle errors accordingly and ensure I’m not using reflection directly where possible.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying class loading for tests**\\n\\nFor my test, the goal is to initialize the class. I can define class bytes from a jar resource within a custom `ClassLoader`, and I might need to define a Proxy. The `ObjectImporter` class implements Serializable and uses only JDK in its static initialization. I need to ensure I'm using a child-first loader since Class.forName won’t return the existing class if I use parent-first. It's also important to catch any potential errors that arise during this process. The complexity lies in dynamic access with Class.forName, and I need to consider how loaders interact with class loading and initialization.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing dynamic class loading challenges**\\n\\nI’m considering whether my agent instruments Class.forName calls in loaded classes. It seems likely, especially if I include a user filter for `javassist.**`. However, in Native Image, I can't define a duplicate class at runtime, so I really need to catch any unsupported errors that arise. If I include a test for defining the duplicate class, it’s important to catch errors and verify Native Image support. I also have to ensure that the class bytes for the `ObjectImporter` resource aren't unintentionally transformed when referencing its initialization.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating class initialization**\\n\\nI'm considering how the one-argument Class.forName initializes with the caller loader. If a class is currently being initialized, it returns that class instead of redefining it. I'm wondering if Class.forName in a test might duplicate this initialization.\\n\\nNow, in a native image scenario, defining the ObjectImporter from bytes brings up concerns about dynamic class loading. The classBytes from resources may not be included, and I could explore using getResourceAsStream. But resources in a native image might be missing, which could lead to exceptions. I need to ensure we don't fail when dealing with native setups.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Updating imports**\\n\\nI need to add the org.graalvm import after the java in the org group. I should also make use of the existing IOException. I think I'll edit by removing the MethodHandle imports and testing that. Additionally, I'll bring in the NativeImageSupport import and create a new test and loader. It seems like a good plan to ensure everything is organized and functional!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_NIF1Bp4ZViqWDB4wJp8gXFTb|fc_0198b27cdb59b2d30169feeaf4ee0c819e93f15fc28cd33076", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.jboss.weld/weld-osgi-bundle/1.1.0.Final/src/test/java/org_jboss_weld/weld_osgi_bundle/ObjectImporterTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.lang.invoke.MethodHandle;\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodHandles;\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodType;\n", "newText": ""}, {"oldText": "import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n", "newText": "import org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    void compilerGeneratedClassResolverUsesClassForName() throws Throwable {\n        MethodHandles.Lookup lookup = MethodHandles.privateLookupIn(ObjectImporter.class, MethodHandles.lookup());\n        MethodHandle resolver = lookup.findStatic(\n                ObjectImporter.class,\n                \"class$\",\n                MethodType.methodType(Class.class, String.class));\n\n        Class<?> resolvedClass = (Class<?>) resolver.invoke(ObjectImporter.class.getName());\n\n        assertThat(resolvedClass).isSameAs(ObjectImporter.class);\n    }\n\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    void staticInitializerUsesCompilerGeneratedClassResolver() throws Exception {\n        IsolatedObjectImporterClassLoader classLoader = new IsolatedObjectImporterClassLoader(\n                ObjectImporterTest.class.getClassLoader());\n        try {\n            Class<?> reloadedClass = Class.forName(ObjectImporter.class.getName(), true, classLoader);\n\n            assertThat(reloadedClass.getName()).isEqualTo(ObjectImporter.class.getName());\n            assertThat(reloadedClass.getClassLoader()).isSameAs(classLoader);\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1922, "output": 2200, "cacheRead": 43520, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 47642, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778313944861, "responseId": "resp_0198b27cdb59b2d30169feead9850c819e9b0bc90c68c9c227"}}
